 County courthouse in Nogales, Arizona, which borders the much larger city of the same name in Mexico", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018663167/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/77692954", "http://www.loc.gov/item/77692954/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/26d84d9f-4671-5e6d-93b9-6ca2e5c9efd8", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gmd/g4333p.la000006", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/g4333p.la000006/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["roskruge, george j."], "date": "1893", "dates": ["1893"], "description": ["Relief shown by hachures. Shows landownership. \"Copyrighted by George J. Roskruge, Tuscon, Arizona, 1893.\" \"Adopted as the official map of Pima County by resolution of Board of Supervisors, July 22, 1893.\" Includes illus., \"Map of the city of Tucson with additions, 1893,\" and inset of \"Town of Nogales.\" Scale ca. 1:200,000. LC Land ownership maps, 6 Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image. AACR2"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:39:24.076Z", "group": ["gmd.mar", "catalog-split-01", "catalog", "general-maps", "main-catalog-split-01"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/77692954/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd433/g4333/g4333p/la000006.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd433/g4333/g4333p/la000006.gif#h=150&w=278", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd433:g4333:g4333p:la000006/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1109&w=2052", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd433:g4333:g4333p:la000006/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=2218&w=4105"], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["arizona", "nogales", "tucson", "pima county", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["2025-06-07t18:32:05.200000", "2011-11-28t13:39:51", "77692954"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["map"], "partof": ["cultural landscapes", "county landownership maps", "catalog", "geography and map division"], "score": 32.59222, "shelf_id": "G4333.P4 1893 .R6 G4333.P4 1893 .R6 G4333.P4 1893 .R6", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["arizona", "nogales", "tucson (ariz.)", "pima county (ariz.)", "tucson", "pima county", "nogales (ariz.)", "united states", "maps"], "timestamp": "2026-04-29T16:18:09.713Z", "title": "Official map of Pima County, Arizona", "type": ["cartographic"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/77692954/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2020655666", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020655666/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2015028.afc2015028_03002_sr01", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2015028.afc2015028_03002_sr01/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2015028.afc2015028_03002_ms02/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["thomas, charlie (charles, sr.)", "occupational folklife project", "hartmann, nic"], "date": "2015", "dates": ["2015"], "description": ["Charlie Thomas of Thomas Produce in Tucson, Arizona, talks about his life in the fresh produce industry of both North Carolina and Arizona. He discusses his father's and family's involvement in produce industry; handling different vegetables; determining ripeness; changes in industry; the impact of Wal-Mart; growing areas in Mexico; Greco-Mexican connections in produce industry; winter produce and Florida; cash vs. credit; the local industry in Arizona; competition from elsewhere; and etc."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-08-14T14:52:29.355Z", "group": ["afc/2015028", "catalog-split-06", "catalog", "produce-workers", "main-catalog-split-06"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020655666/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:afc:afc2015028:afc2015028_03002:afc2015028_03002_ms02/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg"], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["tucson", "arizona", "nogales"], "mime_type": ["audio/mp3", "application/pdf"], "number": ["online resource", "2021-01-11t12:50:47", "2020655666"], "online_format": ["audio", "pdf"], "original_format": ["sound recording"], "partof": ["american folklife center", "fresh produce workers in arizona: archie green fellows project, 2015-2016", "occupational folklife project", "catalog"], "score": 31.482609, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2020655666", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["produce trade", "occupational training", "oral histories", "social life and customs", "farm produce", "job satisfaction", "sound recordings", "work ethic", "thomas, charlie", "interviews", "quality", "personal narratives", "work environment", "charles, sr.)", "nogales (ariz.)", "arizona", "nogales", "folklore", "quality of work life", "family-owned business enterprises"], "timestamp": "2025-08-14T14:53:11.604Z", "title": "Charles \"Charlie\" Thomas, Sr. interview conducted by Nic Hartmann, 2015-08-25", "type": ["sound recording-nonmusical"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020655666/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2020655667", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020655667/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2015028.afc2015028_03021_sr01", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2015028.afc2015028_03021_sr01/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2015028.afc2015028_03021_ms02/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["hartmann, nic", "cathey, jim", "occupational folklife project"], "date": "2015", "dates": ["2015"], "description": ["Interview with Jim Cathey, Sales and Sourcing Manager of Red Sun Farms in Tubac, Arizona. He talks about entering the industry; moving to Arizona; going into the greenhouse industry; McAllen's (TX) rise as a produce center, and Nogales' response; an average work day; the challenges of the industry; labor and labor shortages; the impact of technology on the trade; and etc."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-08-14T14:52:29.355Z", "group": ["afc/2015028", "catalog-split-07", "catalog", "produce-workers", "main-catalog-split-07"], "hasseg